    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-15T19:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-15T19:16:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/11–1451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Deputy Representative on the North Atlantic Council</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SCM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spofford</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d394fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_PJG1"
                            >Parsons</persName> and cleared with <persName corresp="#p_DEJ1"
                            >Dorsz</persName> of <gloss target="#t_GTI1">GTI</gloss>; repeated to
                        Paris as <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 37, to Ankara, and to
                        Athens.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-15T19:16:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1951—7:16 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 342. Ref <gloss target="#t_Depto1"
                        >Depto</gloss> 616 Nov 14, rptd Paris 1042, Ankara 38, Athens 45.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d394fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Gr <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                    called today and raised question inviting Gr and Turk observers to Rome <gloss
                        target="#t_NAC1">NAC</gloss> mtg.</p>
                <p>We told <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> we feared such action might risk
                    antagonizing Senate fortify opposition there and delay us in common objective
                    bringing Gr and Turk into <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>. Gr <gloss
                        target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> clearly grasped fact we think it unwise have
                    Grks and Turks present Rome but do not know if he will suggest to his Govt
                    withdrawal of request. We did not mention to him our view that reps of countries
                    not bound by <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> engagements shld not be
                    present when Council deals with issues of vital importance to members. As
                    foregoing indicates, this tel confirms attitude expressed to you in <gloss
                        target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 334<note n="3" xml:id="d394fn3">Not
                        printed; it reported the Department of State’s position, which it reaffirmed
                        more strongly this time, that Greek and Turkish observers not be invited to
                        the Rome meetings of the Council. (740.5/11–1351)</note> which crossed
                        <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>.</p>
                <p>You may, of course, tell <persName corresp="#p_PLB1">Pearson</persName> or other
                        <gloss target="#t_Dep1">Dep</gloss>s we shld be glad have Gr and Turk <gloss
                        target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>s Rome invited to opening public session and to
                    social functions (ref para 2; <gloss target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 330, rptd
                    Paris 2870, Athens 2321, Ankara 423<note n="4" xml:id="d394fn4">Not printed, but
                        see footnote 3, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
